title.narrative: Output 2.3 ECD/ECE institutional capacities strengthened to deliver quality early development, learning and school readiness for all, especially most disadvantaged girls and boys

description.narrative: About 6,000 pre-school age children, including children with disabilities, benefited from the draft curriculum and learning materials at ECD/ECE facilities and the capacity building of 110 staff supported by UNICEF. In 2019, the State Pre-school Standards “Pre-school education and child care (0,6 -7 years)” was updated, in line with social cohesion, gender, early intervention approaches, and was submitted for approval to Government. About 27 children with disabilities and 42 parents benefited from services and Individual Family Support Plan developed by Transdisciplinary Team (TDT) within the testing of an Early Identification and Intervention project at a new settlement near to Bishkek. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2020
